    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-15T21:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-15T21:48:00-05:00" n="116"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/82: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-15T21:00:00-05:48">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received February 15, 5.21 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 12th, 4 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me orally that
                    already Honduranean troops have been withdrawn, as promised, only the usual
                    customs guards remaining. Bonilla says that he is studying all day but will
                    leave earlier than first week in March if possible proceeding via Puerto
                    Cortes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
